# Backend Standards

Apply to all backend/domain code in `src/**` and API routes in `app/api/**`.

## Layers
- Keep controllers/route handlers (`app/api/**`) thin. Push logic into use cases (`src/usecases/**`) and domain (`src/domain/**`).

## Ports & Adapters
- Interact with externals via ports (`src/ports/**`) and adapters (`src/adapters/**`).
- Keep side-effects at the edges.

## Validation
- Validate env via `src/lib/env.ts`.
- Validate request DTOs with `zod` where applicable. Fail fast on invalid input.

## Errors
- Use typed errors from `src/lib/errors.ts`.
- Map to proper HTTP status codes in route handlers.
- Never throw raw strings.

## HTTP & Retries
- Use `src/lib/http/fetcher.ts` for timeouts/retries.
- Be explicit about limits and backoff.

## Observability
- Use `src/lib/observability.ts` for request logs and error logs.
- Include contextual metadata (ids, symbols, limits).

## Rate Limiting
- Use `src/lib/rateLimit.ts` for quotas.
- Keep parameters configurable.

## Migrations & Persistence
- If/when a DB is introduced (Prisma/Drizzle), add migration policies and tests before shipping.

## Security
- Never log secrets.
- Read config from env via `getEnv()`.
- Sanitize/validate any user-provided data.

## Documentation
- Update `docs/*` when API shape or behavior changes.
- Document new use cases and ports.
